The paper discusses the use of machine learning algorithms to improve poultry welfare by automatically assessing the health of individual birds. This involves analyzing time series data of chicken behaviors, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
